\begin_layout Definition
Two events 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 are said to be mutually exclusive (or disjoint) if the occurrence of one
 event precludes the occurrence of the other.
 For example, on a single roll of a die, a two and a five cannot both come
 up.
 For a second example, define 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 to be the event that the die is even, and 
\series bold

\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 
\series default
to be the event that the die comes up as a 5.
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset ERT
status open

