\begin_layout Fact*
\begin_inset Formula $P(A\cup B)=P(A)+P(B)-P(A\cap B)$
\end_inset

 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The reason behind this fact is that if there is if 
\begin_inset Formula $A$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $B$
\end_inset

 are not disjoint, then some area is added 
\emph on
twice
\emph default
 when I calculate 
\begin_inset Formula $P\left(A\right)+P\left(B\right)$
\end_inset

.
 To account for this, I simply subtract off the area that was double counted.
\end_layout

