\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula $S$
\end_inset

 is an example of a 
\series bold
Binomial Random Variable.

\series default
 A binomial experiment is one that:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Experiment consists of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 identical trials
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
Each trial results in one of two outcomes (Heads/Tails, presence/absence).
 One will be labeled a success and the other a failure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The probability of success on a single trial is equal to 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 and remains the same from trial to trial.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The trials are independent (this is implied from property 3)
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
The random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 is the number of successes observed during 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 trials
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Recall that the probability mass function (pmf) describes how the probability
 is spread across the possible outcomes, and in this case, I can describe
 this via a nice formula.
 The pmf of a a binomial random variable 
\begin_inset Formula $Y$
\end_inset

 taken from 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

 trials each with probability of success 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi$
\end_inset

 is 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
P(Y=y)=\underbrace{\frac{n!}{y!(n-y)!}}_{orderings}\;\underbrace{\pi^{y}}_{y\, successes}\;\underbrace{(1-\pi)^{n-y}}_{n-y\, failures}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
where we define 
\begin_inset Formula $n!=n(n-1)\dots(2)(1)$
\end_inset

 and further define 
\begin_inset Formula $0!=1$
\end_inset

.
 Often the ordering term is written more compactly as 
\begin_inset Formula ${n \choose y}=\frac{n!}{y!\left(n-y\right)!}$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There will be a variety of distributions we'll be interested in and R refers
 to them using the following abbreviations
\begin_inset Newline newline
\end_inset


\begin_inset Box Frameless
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
has_inner_box 1
inner_pos "t"
use_parbox 0
use_makebox 0
width "100col%"
special "none"
height "1in"
height_special "totalheight"
status open

