\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

         main='Binomial Distribution(n=20,p=0.1)', 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

         ylab='Probability', xlab='Number Sites Occupied')
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout

@
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Often we are interested in questions such as 
\begin_inset Formula $P(Y\le2)$
\end_inset

 which is the probability that we see 2 or fewer of the sites being occupied
 by mountain chickadee.
 These calculations can be tedious to calculate by hand but R will calculate
 these cumulative distribution function values for you using the 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

p-function
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 This cumulative distribution function gives the sum of all values up to
 and including the number given.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Box Frameless
position "t"
hor_pos "c"
