\begin_layout Enumerate
During a road bike race, there is always a chance a crash will occur.
 Suppose the probability that at least one crash will occur in any race
 I'm in is 
\begin_inset Formula $\pi=0.2$
\end_inset

 and that races are independent.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
What is the probability that the next two races I'm in will both have crashes?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
What is the probability that neither of my next two races will there be
 a crash?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Enumerate
What is the probability that at least one of the next two races will have
 a crash?
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
My cats suffer from gastric distress due to eating house plants and the
 number of vomits per week that I have to clean up follows a Poisson distributio
n with rate 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda=1.2$
\end_inset

.
 
\end_layout

